I was coding a part of my game and got stuck when I tested it.  It was a very easy code, like: If player has &quot;object&quot; than print... and turn flag on.  I had the object, but the game wouldn't print...  I scanned my code and scanned my code and scanned my........ you get the picture.

The problem: if got &lt;object&gt; then {msg &lt;words...&gt;
flag on &lt;flag&gt;
}

The solution: if got &lt;object&gt; then {
msg &lt;words...&gt;
flag on &lt;flag&gt;
}


See the difference?  I browsed through the ASL Guide under &quot;Braces&quot; and found a section that didn't mention this very small, but important rule.


-Witch
